{
  "stem": "10572.6",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Anybody who has ever been in Elkhart, Indiana-- and I wasn't quite sure if I had been so wise to survive Buchenwald to end up in Elkhart.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The heat of the summer, slept with the-- without any air conditioner-- any.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was pretty horrible.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And about a week later, a letter was forward to me from Palm Springs, California, Mrs.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Hamilton, with a check in it for $700 as a loan so that I could buy the passage for my parents.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I took that as an indication of the earlier imperative, go west, young man.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I got on the bus and had told Orry Goldberg that I was leaving Elkhart.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And Orry Goldberg assured me that someday I could be king in Alkhart but I would be a schnorrer in Chicago.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I told him that I didn't believe in monarchy anyhow and would-- [LAUGHS]-- give up to be a king in Elkhart.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I left.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And wonderfully enough, that when I went in the Army, Mrs.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Goldberg gave blood to the American Red Cross in my name.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I went to Chicago, and booked out the passage for my parents, used the $700, and then tried to find a job in Chicago.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that became very, very difficult for all kinds of reasons that I don't necessarily want to go into.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, there was some social workers at the Jewish Committee on 130 Northwest Street who told me that I was not justified to come to Chicago, that I belonged to Indiana because I had been sent to Indiana.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I told Miss [?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Sabbath ?], the granddaughter of Judge [?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Sabbath ?], that I was not a piece of luggage that could be shipped back and forth, and I would stay in Chicago.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
